It will slaughter all chickens in local chicken farms and all poultry at wholesale markets and retail outlets in an attempt to get rid of the source of influenza A H5N1 virus or " bird flu . "
Hong Kong's neighbor city of Shenzhen has not discovered any case of H5N1 virus infection at its 200 poultry farms, according to a local official in charge of animal epidemics.
Macao is prepared for any possible outbreak of the bird flu although no case of H5N1 virus has been found.
